army spokesmen said the shootings were being investigated
the arab-run palestinian press service said jewish settlers had tried to enter the village after nightfall and were turned away by the 3,000 residents
soldiers arrived about 8 p.m. and clashed with villagers who hurled stones. they fired flares to provide light and later opened fire with live ammunition, the agency said
israel radio said arab demonstrators blocked a main highway outside the village and stoned israeli soldiers. it said a number of jewish settlers also arrived on the scene. shots were fired, and the army was investigating the source of the gunfire, israel radio added
the palestine press identified the two dead as raed mahmoud awad barghouti, 17, who was shot in the head, and ahmed ibrahim mustafa al barghouti, 22, who was wounded in the stomach
the deaths brought to 74 the number of arabs killed by israeli gunfire and beatings since anti-occupation rioting erupted dec. 8, according to u.n. figures. hundreds more have been wounded
before flying to cairo, shultz met separately with shamir and foreign minister shimon peres, who told reporters the negotiations were complicated ``but not hopeless'' despite rejections by jordan and syria on saturday
nothing is dead, and nothing is at a dead end. it is a very complicated issue. it may take time,'' peres said
