the leader of the main opposition social democrat populist party stepped down sunday as party chairman, the anatolia news agency said
the agency said erdal inonu, son of the late president ismet inonu, did not give a reason for his resignation from the party post. he was elected chairman in may 1986
anatolia said that after inonu announced his resignation, the party's secretary-general, fikri saglar, announced that he also would give up his post
the agency said that inonu told reporters that he also would resign as a member of parliament. but hikmet cetin, deputy head of the party's parliamentary group, later announced that inonu retracted that decision
the social democrat populist party was formed in december 1985 by a merger of the social democratic party and the populist party. it has 99 deputies in turkey's 450-member parliament
four dominican stowaways who were locked in the cargo hold of a container ship set a fire to get the crew's attention, but the blaze burned out of control, the coast guard said
coast guard spokesman alan burd said no one was injured in the fire aboard the 560-foot nedlloyd singapore
when the ship's crew went in to fight the fire, they found four dominicans that had stowed away in the ship's last port of call,'' he said. ``it appears that the four stowaways set the fire intentionally to attract the crew's attention because they were locked in this cargo hold.''
burd said the dominicans were rescued unharmed and turned over to local police
one crew member fell while fighting the fire and appeared to have broken a leg, but no other injuries were reported
the dominicans boarded the ship friday night in the dominican republic port of haina, about 10 miles west of the capital santo domingo, a spokesman for the puerto rico police department said. it docked in san juan early sunday
burd said the fire was first reported around 2:30 a.m. and raged out of control about an hour later
there was no immediate estimate of damages
five people were killed and 28 were injured, 14 seriously, when the bus they were in missed a curve and plunged off a highway, police said sunday
the accident occurred on the tibet highway saturday. the passenger bus was headed to lamosanghu from katmandu, a 50-mile drive
