an ethiopian airlines pilot trainee landed a small plane at khartoum airport and asked for asylum in sudan, an official source said sunday
the source said gabre getahon, 22, was handed over to sudanese security authorities and the cessna, which belonged to ethiopian airlines, was under guard at the airport
other sources said getahon decided to defect to sudan on saturday, while on a training flight in the small aircraft
he was quoted as saying that he first planned to land at ed-damazin, in southeastern sudan near the ethiopian border, but could not land there because of maintenance operations under way at the airport. he then followed the blue nile to khartoum airport, where he put down the plane
the sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said getahon is from tigre province in northern ethiopia, where a rebellion has been going on for years
he told sudanese authorities he fled to escape ``repression'' in his homeland, the sources said
he also reportedly claimed to have made several previous defection attempts via kenya before joining the airline but was caught and returned to ethiopia
