the blaze in paris' 12th district, in the southeast part of the city, started in a second-floor apartment and spread through the six-story building via the wooden elevator cage, officials said
up to 100 firefighters battled the flames, containing them in about an hour, by 6 a.m
five people died in the flames and 10 others suffered burns, smoke inhalation or fractured bones from jumping from windows, according to rescue workers
about 40 people lived in the building, which was destroyed
